title.narrative: Increased country-level capacities (Government and communities) to respond to emergencies are increased, with 120,000 children accessing education in emergency situations, including IDPs, host communities and returnees.

description.narrative: UNICEF provided education emergency programming for 59,202 vulnerable children (46% or 27,354 girls) affected by humanitarian crises. These affected girls and boys benefitted with a comprehensive education package comprising of teaching and learning materials, access to school feeding and safe drinking water, trained teachers who receive 18 days of in-service teacher training on pedagogical skills and who receive incentives and support by capable Community Education Committees members. These children benefitted from recreational supplies and girls also receive menstrual hygiene kits and menstrual health management support. These girls and boys also receive psychosocial support through trained teachers and CEC members | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
